<SampleDescription>
   <p>This sample demonstrates the hamburger mode in the Menu component. </p> 
</SampleDescription>
<ActionDescription>
   <p>Enabling the <code><a target="_blank" href="https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/blazor/Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfMenu-1.html#Syncfusion_Blazor_Navigations_SfMenu_1_HamburgerMode" aria-label="HamburgerMode">HamburgerMode</a></code> property makes the Menu component in adaptive view. By default, it shows header with hamburger icon in <b>Horizontal</b> orientation.</p>
   <p>The Menu appears on clicking the hamburger icon. You can use the <code><a target="_blank" href="https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/blazor/Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfMenu-1.html#Syncfusion_Blazor_Navigations_SfMenu_1_OpenAsync" aria-label="OpenAsync">OpenAsync</a></code> and <code><a target='_blank' href='https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/blazor/Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfMenu-1.html#Syncfusion_Blazor_Navigations_SfMenu_1_CloseAsync' aria-label="CloseAsync">CloseAsync</a></code> methods to show/hide the Menu programmatically.</p>
   <p>More information about Blazor Menu component can be found in this <a target="_blank" href="https://blazor.syncfusion.com/documentation/menu-bar/usecase-scenario#hamburger-menu"  aria-label="documentation section"> documentation </a>section.</p>
</ActionDescription>

